Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize is part of a panel discussion on the  COVID-19 pandemic and flattening the curve. Dr Zweli Mkhize is addressing the importance of primary care doctors during this time. Others on the panel are Prof Salim Abdool Karim – Epidemiologist, ID specialist and chair of the Presidential Advisory Committee,  Prof Guy Richards – Emeritus Prof critical care Wits University and  Dr David Jankelow- President of the SA Heart Association and Cardiologist Netcare Linksfield Clinics. Below is the stream: 